In response to your auto reply to my inquiry about my order placed on
December 25, the attached screenshot is what I get when I attempt to track
my order. I'm not looking for a refund of a product I've received. I'm
looking for a refund of a product I've "NOT" received within the 7 days as
promised. I have not moved so therefore no need to change my address as you
received the correct one. I can't pick it up from the post office if there
is nothing there to pick up. I would receive a notification from them if I
had a parcel to pick up and I have not. My payment was accepted. I sent you
a copy of my bank statement showing you took the payment so my payment
never failed. I do not need info about the product as I know what I
ordered. Please do not send me another useless auto reply. I give you until
Friday the 18th of January to resolve this by either sending me a full
refund to the same card you received it from or telling me when my order is
arriving. If I have not heard from you by that time I will have to have my
bank reverse the payment sent to you.
Orla McCready

column4: Re: Can you help me please? Re JJD0002219701503138 track no
column6:
Shōujù biānhào wèiyú zhǔtí xíng zhōng de diànzǐ yóujiàn dǐngbù.

Wúlùn rúhé, nǐ yīnggāi nénggòu zài nǐ de jìlù zhōng zhǎodào tā. Zhè yěshì wǒ zhīqián tōngguò diànzǐ yóujiàn fāsòng de xìnjiàn.


Wǒ bù xīwàng yǒurén liánxì wǒ, yīnwèi tuìhuí de wùpǐn jiàgé wèi 99 biànshì, ér 39 yīngbàng zé shì tōngguò wǒ de xìnyòngkǎ zhīfù de.


Nǐ de guǎnggào shì yòng yú yīgè cricut wúxiàn kōngqì liǎng tái dǎyìnjī ér bùshì yī jiàn dài yǒu diāokè de fúshì shǒushì,“ài nǐ dào yuèqiú hé bèibù”. Yā wényín sèdiào jīnshǔ.


 Háo wú yíwèn, qítā rén yǐjīng wèi cǐ ér duòluò,“piànjú” bìngqiě yǐjīng shōu dàole tāmen de “ài nǐ dào yuèqiú hé bèibù” zhuì shì, wǒ xiāngxìn nǐ bìxū fà xiàn zhè yīqiè dōu hěn yǒuqù.


Duì wǒ huò qítā rén lái shuō, zhè duìyú nàxiē bìxū wèi zìjǐ de qián ér nǔlì gōngzuò de rén lái shuō bìng bùshì “yǒuqù”. Wǒ shì cánjí rén, wúfǎ zài jiànkāng zhuàngkuàng bù jiā de qíngkuàng xià gōngzuò, zhè shì lìng rén jǔsàng hé bù gōngpíng de, gèng bùyòng shuō tā ràng wǒ gǎnjué dào de fāngshìle. Yīgè wánquán báichī.


Wǒ jué bùshì yīgè “báichī”, dàn juédé wǒ bèi xuǎn wéi yīgè zhǐshì yīnwèi wǒ yǐwéi wǒ huì mǎi xiē dōngxī huàn yīgè.


Wǒ yǐjīng zài wǒ de xìnyòngkǎ gōngsī zhùcèle zhège qīzhà xíngwéi, yīnwèi wǒ xiànzài rènwéi nǐ gēnběn méiyǒu huídá wǒ zhīqián de wèntí ér wú yìxiàng wǒ tígōng nǐ suǒ xuānchuán de shāngpǐn. Wǒ zhēnchéng dìnggòu de shíjì dǎyìnjī zài nǎlǐ?


Nǐ méiyǒu huídá zhège wèntí de yuányīn shì yīnwèi wǒ xiànzài xiāngxìn nǐ bùnéng. Méiyǒu dǎyìnjī, wǒ bù huì shōu dào wǒ dìnggòu de shāngpǐn.


Zhèxiē dǎyìnjī de língshòu jià wèi 249 bàng yǐshàng, wǒ fāxiàn zhè shì lìng yīgè yuányīn, wǒ xiāngxìn wǒ bù huì yǐ 39.50 De jiàgé cóng nǐ nàlǐ shōu dào zhè tái dǎyìnjī. Wǒ jiǎnchále nǐ suǒwèi de wǎngzhàn, zài nàlǐ kàn bù dào zhèxiē dǎyìnjī chūshòu.


Nàlǐ. Wǒ gǎnjué hǎoduōle, xiànzài wǒ yǐjīng yǒule zhège páoxiāo érqiě méiyǒu jìnyībù de fánnǎo, chúfēi nǐ zhēn de yāo duì cǐ cǎiqǔ xíngdòng bìng bǎ shìqíng zuò hǎo, fǒuzé bù huì làngfèi nǐ de shíjiān.


Bùzhī hégù, wǒ duì cǐ biǎoshì huáiyí.


Kǎ luó ěr hú


收据编号位于主题行中的电子邮件顶部。

无论如何，你应该能够在你的记录中找到它。这也是我之前通过电子邮件发送的信件。


我不希望有人联系我，因为退回的物品价格为99便士，而39英镑则是通过我的信用卡支付的。


你的广告是用于一个cricut无线空气两台打印机而不是一件带有雕刻的服饰首饰，“爱你到月球和背部”。压纹银色调金属。


 毫无疑问，其他人已经为此而堕落，“骗局”并且已经收到了他们的“爱你到月球和背部”坠饰，我相信你必须发现这一切都很有趣。


对我或其他人来说，这对于那些必须为自己的钱而努力工作的人来说并不是“有趣”。我是残疾人，无法在健康状况不佳的情况下工作，这是令人沮丧和不公平的，更不用说它让我感觉到的方式了。一个完全白痴。


我绝不是一个“白痴”，但觉得我被选为一个只是因为我以为我会买些东西换一个。


我已经在我的信用卡公司注册了这个欺诈行为，因为我现在认为你根本没有回答我之前的问题而无意向我提供你所宣传的商品。我真诚订购的实际打印机在哪里？


你没有回答这个问题的原因是因为我现在相信你不能。没有打印机，我不会收到我订购的商品。


这些打印机的零售价为249磅以上，我发现这是另一个原因，我相信我不会以39.50的价格从你那里收到这台打印机。我检查了你所谓的网站，在那里看不到这些打印机出售。


那里。我感觉好多了，现在我已经有了这个咆哮而且没有进一步的烦恼，除非你真的要对此采取行动并把事情做好，否则不会浪费你的时间。


不知何故，我对此表示怀疑。


卡罗尔湖

Carol xx

column4: Re: Can you help me please? Re JJD0002219701503138 track no
column6:
The receipt number is at the top of my email in the subject line.
You should be able to find this within your records anyway. It is also in my previous correspondence via email.

I do not want someone to contact me regarding returning an item that costs 99 pence for the 39 pounds fifty that you have been paid via my credit card.

Your advertisement was for a cricut wireless air two printer not a piece of costume jewellery with an engraving, ‘Love you to the moon and back’. Embossed on silver toned metal.

 No doubt others have fallen for this, ‘scam’ and have since received their, ‘Love you to the moon and back’ pendant and I feel sure you must find this all so amusing.

It is not, ‘amusing’ to me or the others that you have done this to who have to work very hard for their money. I am disabled and unable to work through ill health and this is so frustrating and unfair, not to mention the way it has made me feel. A complete idiot.

I am by no means an, ‘idiot’ but feel I have been taken for one just because I thought I would buy myself something for a change.

I have registered this with my credit card company as fraudulent as I now believe that you have no intention of supplying me with the goods that you advertised at all as you have not answered my previous question at all. Where is the actual printer that I ordered in good faith?

The reason why you have not answered this question is because I now believe that you can’t. There is no printer and I am not going to receive the item that I ordered.

These printers retail at 249 pounds and up I have since discovered and that is another reason why I believe I will not be receiving this printer from you at the cost of 39.50. I have checked your so called website and can see none of these printers on there for sale.

There. I feel so much better now I have had this rant and without further ado, will waste no more time with you people unless you are actually going to do something about this and put things right.

Somehow, I doubt it.

Carol L

Good day,

I have recently attempted to purchase one of your products, Laundry Folding Machine.  Because I live on the Isle of Man, a UK island, I understand that delivery is extremely challenging and most company’s, except the the major countries in the world, will not deliver there.  Therefore, I used my sister’s address in mainland United Kingdom, with my own address as the payment on my VISA DEBIT card.

However, probably because of this difference in delivery address and card address the payment is declined, saying it is a risk.

We all know that a DEBIT card is instantaneous deductions of funds at the time of payment, so there is no risk on the card, as it will immediately tell the seller that the charge has gone through and the money deducted right then and there.  So I can only assume it is the disparity between delivery and payment addresses.

I purchase large amounts of goods from around the world, including China, one of the most difficult countries to purchase from with my address, as they cannot find the Isle of Man and therefore, it doesn’t exist.  I assure you that it does, but shouldn’t be a factor in this purchase as I am using my sisters address in the United Kingdom.
